The paper discusses the problem of setting prices in an electronic market, which is a topic that falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and electronic commerce (cs.EC). The use of submodular valuations and the focus on maximizing profit suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing conditions for equilibrium, which could involve the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
